Colloquial translation issues
by student_8 » Tue 11.16.2010 3:39 pm The most difficult area of study, in my experience, is learning colloquial language. I find that this is covered extremely poorly in virtually every textbook I have ever come across. Once you start trying to read manga, you realize just how little you really know.Now, I do not wish to be an "annoying" poster who asks a bunch of questions that have already been covered somewhere or other on the boards. However, there are a great deal of threads here and it would be difficult to trawl through every single one looking for a particular issue. What I want to ask is whether it would be acceptable to ask a question if I cannot find anything related to it using the Search facility. I have already tried entering a few expressions into the search, and most of them didn't seem to come up. Maybe I am doing somethiung wrong?-Arch
